  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators' aim is to study the effect of pressure support ventilation at two levels
      of PEEP and Pressure Support versus neurally adjusted ventilatory assist (NAVA) in COPD
      patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In this study, two levels of pressure support and PEEP during pressure support ventilation
      are compared with neurally adjusted ventilatory assist (NAVA) in COPD patients by measuring
      respiratory mechanics, intrinsic PEEP, work of breathing and patient's level of comfort.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
